I"c·<h1 id="buttons">Buttons</h1>

<p>React-Admin provides button components for all the common uses.</p>

<h2 id="navigation-buttons">Navigation Buttons</h2>

<p>These buttons allow users to navigate between the various react-admin views.</p>

<h3 id="editbutton"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;EditButton&gt;</code></h3>

<p>Opens the Edit view of a given record:</p>

<div class="language-js highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="k">import</span> <span class="p">{</span> <span class="nx">EditButton</span> <span class="p">}</span> <span class="k">from</span> <span class="dl">'</span><span class="s1">react-admin</span><span class="dl">'</span><span class="p">;</span>

<span class="kd">const</span> <span class="nx">CommentEditButton</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">({</span> <span class="nx">record</span> <span class="p">})</span> <span class="o">=&gt;</span> <span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="nx">EditButton</span> <span class="nx">basePath</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2">/comments</span><span class="dl">"</span> <span class="nx">label</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2">Edit comment</span><span class="dl">"</span> <span class="nx">record</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">{</span><span class="nx">record</span><span class="p">}</span> <span class="sr">/</span><span class="err">&gt;
</span><span class="p">);</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p><img src="./img/edit-button.png" alt="Edit button" /></p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;EditButton&gt;</code> is based on react-admin‚Äôs base <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;Button&gt;</code>, so it‚Äôs responsive, accessible, and the label is translatable.</p>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Prop</th>
      <th>Required</th>
      <th>Type</th>
      <th>Default</th>
      <th>Description</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">basePath</code></td>
      <td>Required</td>
      <td><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">string</code></td>
      <td>-</td>
      <td>Base path to resource, e.g. ‚Äò/posts‚Äô</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">record</code></td>
      <td>Required</td>
      <td><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Object</code></td>
      <td>-</td>
      <td>Record to link to, e.g. <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">{ id: 12, foo: 'bar' }</code></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">label</code></td>
      <td>Optional</td>
      <td><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">string</code></td>
      <td>‚Äòra.action.edit‚Äô</td>
      <td>Label or translation message to use</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">icon</code></td>
      <td>Optional</td>
      <td><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">ReactElement</code></td>
      <td>-</td>
      <td>Icon element, e.g. <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;CommentIcon /&gt;</code></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">scrollToTop</code></td>
      <td>Optional</td>
      <td><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">boolean</code></td>
      <td><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">true</code></td>
      <td>Scroll to top after link</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<p>It also supports <a href="#button">all the other <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;Button&gt;</code> props</a>.</p>

<p><strong>Tip</strong>: You can use it as <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;Datagrid&gt;</code> child with no props, since <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;Datagrid&gt;</code> injects <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">record</code> and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">basePath</code> to its children. However, you should use the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;Datagrid rowClick="edit"&gt;</code> prop instead to avoid using one column for the Edit button.</p>

<p><strong>Tip</strong>: If you want to link to the Edit view manually, use the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">/{resource}/{record.id}</code> location.</p>

<h3 id="showbutton"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;ShowButton&gt;</code></h3>

<p>Opens the Show view of a given record:</p>

<div class="language-js highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="k">import</span> <span class="p">{</span> <span class="nx">ShowButton</span> <span class="p">}</span> <span class="k">from</span> <span class="dl">'</span><span class="s1">react-admin</span><span class="dl">'</span><span class="p">;</span>

<span class="kd">const</span> <span class="nx">CommentShowButton</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">({</span> <span class="nx">record</span> <span class="p">})</span> <span class="o">=&gt;</span> <span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="nx">ShowButton</span> <span class="nx">basePath</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2">/comments</span><span class="dl">"</span> <span class="nx">label</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2">Show comment</span><span class="dl">"</span> <span class="nx">record</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">{</span><span class="nx">record</span><span class="p">}</span> <span class="sr">/</span><span class="err">&gt;
</span><span class="p">);</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p><img src="./img/show-button.png" alt="Show button" /></p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;ShowButton&gt;</code> is based on react-admin‚Äôs base <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;Button&gt;</code>, so it‚Äôs responsive, accessible, and the label is translatable.</p>

